---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
import Header from "../components/Header.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Should I Go Outside?"
  description="Privacy policy for the Should I Go Outside? app and website. We keep it simple: your location is never stored, and we collect only anonymous data to keep the app running well."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="page">
    <div class="card">
      <a href="/" class="brutal-btn brutal-btn--sm back-btn">← Back to home</a>

      <h1 class="heading">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">
        <strong>Should I Go Outside?</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp; shouldigooutside.now<br
        />
        Effective date: March 12, 2026<br />
        Contact: <a href="mailto:contact@toebeans.life" class="link"
          >contact@toebeans.life</a
        >
      </p>

      <p class="intro">
        Should I Go Outside? is built to be simple and respectful of your
        privacy. No accounts, no personal data stored. Here's what happens when
        you use the app or visit this website.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">The short version</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Your location is used only to fetch weather data and is never stored
            or shared beyond that request.
          </li>
          <li>
            We collect anonymous crash reports and usage stats to keep the app
            working well.
          </li>
          <li>
            No account creation. No personal data stored. No selling of your
            data. Ever.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">What the app collects</h2>

        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Your location</h3>
        <p>
          When you use the app, it sends your current location to a third-party
          weather API to fetch conditions for your area. Your location is <strong
            >never stored on our servers</strong
          >, never logged, and never shared with anyone beyond that single
          weather request.
        </p>

        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Crash reports (Firebase Crashlytics)</h3>
        <p>
          We use Firebase Crashlytics to automatically collect anonymous crash
          reports. If the app crashes, we receive a technical stack trace that
          tells us what went wrong. No personal information, no location, no
          identifiers tied to you.
        </p>
        <p>
          Firebase Crashlytics is operated by Google. You can learn more at <a
            href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy"
            class="link"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">firebase.google.com/support/privacy</a
          >.
        </p>

        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Usage analytics (Google Analytics)</h3>
        <p>
          We use Google Analytics to understand how people use the app, like
          which screens are visited and how often the app is opened. All of this
          data is anonymous and aggregated. We cannot identify individual users
          from it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Google Analytics is operated by Google. You can learn more at <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
            class="link"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">policies.google.com/privacy</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">What the website collects</h2>

        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Google Fonts</h3>
        <p>
          This website loads fonts (Lexend Mega and Public Sans) from Google
          Fonts servers. When your browser requests a font file, Google may log
          that request. We don't control those logs. See Google's privacy policy
          for details.
        </p>

        <h3 class="subsection-heading">Cloudflare</h3>
        <p>
          This website is hosted and served through Cloudflare. Cloudflare
          collects standard web server logs (IP address, browser type, pages
          visited, timestamps) as part of normal hosting operations. These logs
          are used for security and performance purposes. See <a
            href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/"
            class="link"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a
          > for details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          The app itself does not set any cookies. Third-party services we use
          (Google Analytics, Firebase) may set their own cookies or use similar
          tracking technologies as part of their standard operation.
        </p>
        <p>
          The website does not set first-party cookies. Cloudflare may set
          security-related cookies as part of their infrastructure.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Who we share data with</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent, or trade your data with anyone. The only sharing
          that happens is your location being sent to a weather API to fetch
          current conditions. The only third parties involved are our analytics
          and crash reporting tools described above.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Should I Go Outside? is available to everyone. Because we don't
          collect any personal information from anyone, there are no special
          restrictions based on age. We have no way to identify whether a user
          is a child, and we collect nothing that would create a privacy risk
          for younger users.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on where you live, you may have rights regarding your
          personal data. Since we don't store any personal data, there's very
          little to act on. Here's how it breaks down:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>GDPR (EU/EEA residents):</strong> You have rights to access, correct,
            or delete your personal data. Since we store none, you'd primarily need
            to contact Google (for Analytics and Crashlytics) directly for any data
            they may hold tied to your device.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>CCPA (California residents):</strong> You have the right to know
            what personal data is collected and to opt out of the sale of your data.
            We collect no personal data and sell nothing. For analytics data, you
            can opt out through Google's privacy settings.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Everyone else:</strong> The above applies to all users regardless
            of jurisdiction.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any rights or ask questions, email us at <a
            href="mailto:contact@toebeans.life"
            class="link">contact@toebeans.life</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Data security</h2>
        <p>
          Since we store nothing, there's nothing to breach on our end. The
          third-party services we use (Google, Cloudflare) have their own
          security practices in place.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If we make meaningful changes to this privacy policy, we'll update the
          effective date at the top.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions or concerns? Reach out to Jordon de Hoog at <a
            href="mailto:contact@toebeans.life"
            class="link">contact@toebeans.life</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="footer-note">
        <a href="/" class="brutal-btn brutal-btn--sm back-btn">← Back to home</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: var(--space-xl) var(--space-md) var(--space-section);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .card {
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-outline);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset-lg) var(--shadow-offset-lg) 0 0
      var(--color-shadow);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-xl) var(--space-xl);
    max-width: 720px;
    width: 100%;
    transform: rotate(-0.5deg);
  }

  .back-btn {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .heading {
    font-family: "Lexend Mega", sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: var(--display-tracking);
    line-height: var(--display-leading);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    border-bottom: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-outline);
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: "Lexend Mega", sans-serif;
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
    border-left: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-primary);
  }

  .subsection-heading {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  ul li {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    position: relative;
  }

  ul li::before {
    content: "→";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-coral);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .link {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-primary);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .link:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-coral);
  }

  .link:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  .footer-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-outline);
  }

  .footer-note .back-btn {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page {
      padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-sm) var(--space-xl);
    }

    .card {
      padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-md);
      transform: none;
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .link {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>
